  "debug_data_path": "debug_data/2020_705",
  "eprint": {
    "title": "On the minimal value set size of APN functions",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Ingo Czerwinski",
        "email": "ingo@czerwinski",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "We give a lower bound for the size of the value set of\nalmost perfect nonlinear (APN) functions \\(F\\colon \\mathbb{F}_2^n \\to \\mathbb{F}_2^n\\)\nin explicit form and proof it with methods of linear programming.\nIt coincides with the bound given in [CHP17].\nFor \\(n\\) even it is \\(\\frac{ 2^n + 2 }{3}\\) and sharp as the simple example \\(F(x) = x^3\\) shows.\nThe sharp lower bound for \\(n\\) odd has to lie between \\(\\frac{ 2^n + 1 }{3}\\) and \\(2^{n-1}\\).\nSharp bounds for the cases \\(n = 3\\) and \\(n = 5\\) are explicitly given.",
    "keywords": [
      "Boolean functions",
      "Cryptographic S-boxes",
      "Almost perfect nonlinear (APN)",
      "Value set size"
    ],
    "category": "Foundations",
    "publication_info": "Preprint. MINOR revision.",
    "last_updated": "2021-05-05",
